♪ Nowhere ♪

01:39.391 --> 01:41.351
♪ Nowhere ♪♪

01:43.437 --> 01:47.566
If your son goes to Camp Microchipewa,
he'll learn more than just computer skills.

01:47.733 --> 01:49.484
How about basketball?
That's right.

01:49.651 --> 01:54.239
Learn to shoot like Akeem and the Shaq, once
counselor Dave shows you the trajectory.

01:54.406 --> 01:57.701
If you're hungry,
Fridays are international fiesta days...

01:57.868 --> 01:59.870
featuring foods from
all over the world,

02:00.037 --> 02:03.332
including this favorite
from Italy... pizza.

02:03.498 --> 02:07.836
Whoops! It's awards day already.
The summer sure has flown by.

02:08.002 --> 02:11.632
At Microchipewa, you'll leave
with good friends, good memories...

02:11.798 --> 02:14.509
and a better understanding
of the job skills of the future.

02:14.676 --> 02:17.763
That's right.
Who says computers have to be boring?

02:17.929 --> 02:22.601
At Microchipewa Computer Camp, we say
that computers are really not... boring.

02:22.768 --> 02:27.064
Boy, I wish they had camps
like that when I was a kid.

02:27.230 --> 02:29.524
Sounds great, huh, Morris?

02:29.691 --> 02:31.401
It sounds fantastic!

02:31.568 --> 02:33.111
I'm in hell. Shoot me.

02:35.197 --> 02:36.448
So, did you decide about camp yet?

02:36.615 --> 02:40.243
That guy from MicroCamp swears they're getting
CD-ROMs with double-speed interfaces.

02:40.410 --> 02:45.123
- Sounds excellent, huh, Mud?
- Yo, dog breath... stay!

02:45.290 --> 02:48.877
Not you, Walter.
I want Mud.

02:49.044 --> 02:51.838
You're not supposed to
be in this hallway, pud.

02:52.005 --> 02:54.007
- Pud!
- Come on, stop it.

02:54.174 --> 02:55.342
What a dork!

02:55.509 --> 02:58.553
Hands off, Tim.
This little turd is mine.

02:58.720 --> 03:01.640
You need a bath, man,
in the porcelain jacuzzi.

03:04.142 --> 03:06.228
Don't let anybody in.

03:11.817 --> 03:13.902
All right, midget.
You got it?

03:16.071 --> 03:19.157
Damn!

03:19.324 --> 03:24.162
Here. You read The Red Badge
of Courage by Stephen Crane.

03:24.329 --> 03:26.581
I analyzed his depiction
of the Civil War.

03:26.748 --> 03:29.418
Uh, so who do I say won?

03:29.584 --> 03:33.046
- You went for the North.
- Okay.

03:33.213 --> 03:36.466
Anyway, I say it's good for a C+, easy.

03:36.633 --> 03:38.969
Cool, but make the next one a "B."

03:39.136 --> 03:40.804
So, how you doin', Mud?

03:40.971 --> 03:43.473
I'm okay.

03:43.640 --> 03:46.977
That musclehead in gym class tried
to hang me up by my underwear again.

03:47.144 --> 03:51.857
Wayne Fletcher? Don't worry. I've
got him covered. Okay, let's do it.

03:52.023 --> 03:54.818
Zack, do we have to?

03:54.985 --> 03:59.114
Look, Mud, I've told you a thousand times.
I've got a reputation.

04:02.909 --> 04:05.328
Oh-ho, Zack! Please stop it! Oh!

04:05.495 --> 04:08.331
Please, don't stick
my head in the toilet.

04:08.498 --> 04:11.752
I won't use the hallway again.

04:11.918 --> 04:13.003
Stylin', Mud.

04:13.170 --> 04:16.130
Yup. It's that
just flushed look.

04:16.298 --> 04:17.466
Looks good.

04:19.259 --> 04:20.510
- Call me later.
- Okay. Bye.

04:20.677 --> 04:22.804
- Call me later.
- Bye.

04:22.971 --> 04:26.767
If that idiot Epstein
gives us another grammar quiz,

04:26.933 --> 04:29.311
I swear I'm gonna wind up in
English as a Second Language.

04:29.478 --> 04:31.688
Or you'll have to take it
over in summer school.

04:31.855 --> 04:33.273
I'm already going
to summer school.

04:33.440 --> 04:34.483
Another computer camp?

04:34.649 --> 04:39.070
Yup. My parents won't be happy till I'm the
poster child for the "Adopt a Dork Foundation."

04:39.237 --> 04:43.784
Yeah, well, better than Camp Broadway.
"Did you get that Clearasil commercial?"

04:43.950 --> 04:47.829
Well, I'm up for Spaghetti-O's
Extra Meaty. Tres dull.

04:47.996 --> 04:50.290
Oh, Gaby, when's your mom
leaving for the islands?

04:50.457 --> 04:53.835
Right after she puts me
on the bus to Camp Slenderella.

04:54.002 --> 04:56.671
Oh, gross! Celery sticks
and rice cakes again?

04:56.838 --> 04:58.215
Prison food.

04:58.381 --> 04:59.758
I'll mail you a Twinkie.

04:59.925 --> 05:01.259
Thanks for waiting, guys.

05:01.426 --> 05:03.428
Yeah, well, you were busy
with your new delinquent friends.

05:03.595 --> 05:05.138
Trish, we're not
delinquent friends!

05:05.305 --> 05:06.389
Oh, yeah?

05:06.556 --> 05:10.435
Then how come you get sent to military camp
every summer? 'Cause you like the haircuts?

05:10.602 --> 05:15.065
You know my dad.
Builds character, Zachary.

05:15.232 --> 05:16.691
It's for your own good, Gab.

05:16.858 --> 05:19.528
But, Trish,
all the other kids are going.

05:19.694 --> 05:22.030
Wait, how 'bout this one?
It'll be fun.

05:22.197 --> 05:23.281
Yeah.

05:23.448 --> 05:25.700
Can you believe what Arnold brought
to school today? It was disgusting.

05:25.867 --> 05:26.952
It was degrading.

05:27.118 --> 05:28.954
That was cool!
That was really cool!

05:29.120 --> 05:30.163
That was so gross.

05:30.330 --> 05:31.998
- He needs help.
- He is beyond help.

05:32.165 --> 05:35.377
But, Morris, it'll be fun.

05:35.544 --> 05:39.172
Dad, all those computer camps
are nerd rehab centers.

05:39.339 --> 05:42.217
I just want to play baseball.
Have some real fun.

05:42.384 --> 05:45.262
The DOS tutorial isn't fun?

05:45.428 --> 05:48.807
Come on. Look, I wouldn't
steer you wrong.

05:48.974 --> 05:53.103
I know you think I'm an old fogey but your
old man still knows how to cut loose.

05:53.270 --> 05:56.398
Look, Morris, they have those
low-fat, sugar-free macaroons.

05:56.565 --> 06:01.111
Not only the best tasting, pasteurized,
processed, non-dairy imitation...

06:01.278 --> 06:03.655
semi-cheese product,

06:03.822 --> 06:06.658
but also the healthiest.

06:06.825 --> 06:10.036
Now, I'm not a licensed physician, but
I've been to my share of free clinics.

06:10.203 --> 06:13.206
Each serving of Miracle Cheese
contains no sodium, no glucose,

06:13.373 --> 06:15.500
no "mucose" and absolutely
no cholesterol.

06:15.667 --> 06:18.628
Let's talk about
breadstick safety.

06:18.795 --> 06:24.259
Your basic sesame breadstick.
No, it looks harmless enough.

06:24.426 --> 06:27.387
But what if you lose control
at high speeds?

06:27.554 --> 06:31.600
- - Easy Cheese comes in these...

06:31.766 --> 06:34.394
Now, Morris, I don't want to be
one of those pushy parents.

06:34.561 --> 06:36.146
It's too late.

06:36.313 --> 06:38.106
Now, what is that supposed
to mean, young man?

06:38.273 --> 06:40.609
I mean, what if I don't want
to go to computer camp?

06:40.775 --> 06:43.528
Morris, there are plenty of things
I'd rather do with $3,000.

06:43.695 --> 06:45.196
Me too.

06:45.363 --> 06:47.240
Havarti and Gorgonzola!

06:47.407 --> 06:48.700
Come on.

06:48.867 --> 06:50.076
Wait a minute!
You are thinking...

06:50.243 --> 06:54.080
cheese with... fish.

06:54.247 --> 06:56.458
Baa-aad.

06:56.625 --> 06:58.335
Morris!

06:58.501 --> 07:02.088
Well, let's go right to the source.

07:04.007 --> 07:06.259
Is it just me,
or it dry in here?

07:06.426 --> 07:08.219
Thank you very much.

07:08.386 --> 07:10.972
Be kind to your waitress.

07:11.139 --> 07:13.308
Good night, everybody.

07:17.520 --> 07:20.357
- Morris.
- Not the "potential" thing again?

07:20.523 --> 07:23.526
But that's just what
you've got: potential.

07:23.693 --> 07:27.113
Anyway, so after all that, he
lays the money guilt thing on me.

07:27.280 --> 07:28.865
You know, camps cost
thousands of dollars.

07:29.032 --> 07:30.200
Yeah.

07:30.367 --> 07:34.245
I say, give me the money, I'll buy a Harley
and I'll be outta your way the whole summer.

07:34.412 --> 07:36.915
With that kind of money,
we could just rent our own camp.

07:37.082 --> 07:38.541
I'd buy a new wardrobe.

07:38.708 --> 07:39.751
I'd buy The Gap.

07:39.918 --> 07:42.253
Whoa! Whoa! What'd you say?

07:42.420 --> 07:45.256
Oh, I said, for that kind of
money, we could rent our own camp.

07:45.423 --> 07:47.759
- It's brilliant!
- It's deranged!

07:47.926 --> 07:51.596
- It's suicide.
- Besides, we need an adult to pull it off.

07:51.763 --> 07:53.390
But we're adults,
one for each camp.

07:53.556 --> 07:55.058
And one really twisted one.

07:55.225 --> 07:59.813
- Who's gonna rent a cabin...
- What'd you just say?

07:59.980 --> 08:02.941
Did you guys hear about the guy who
taught drama before Mr. Ellison?

08:03.108 --> 08:05.777
Yeah, my sister had him.
Tres bizarre, she said.

08:05.944 --> 08:08.989
He tried to do Silence of
the Lambs as a musical.

08:09.155 --> 08:11.825
Anyway, he got fired
and left town.

08:11.992 --> 08:15.120
Yeah, well, he got fired, but
I'm not so sure he left town.

08:15.286 --> 08:17.247
The cheese guy?

08:18.415 --> 08:21.626
Okay, let's
do it. Mud.

08:37.892 --> 08:39.269
Hi.

08:39.811 --> 08:41.895
Can I help you?

08:42.063 --> 08:45.483
Yeah, uh... Is your name
Dennis Van Welker?

08:45.650 --> 08:49.070
No. Just inspectin' the hinges here.

08:50.697 --> 08:54.367
Look at that.
Low carbon content.

08:57.162 --> 09:00.874
- Uh, ooh. Are you sure your name isn't
Dennis Van Welker? -

09:02.250 --> 09:04.502
He used to be a
drama teacher at King Junior High.

09:04.669 --> 09:08.131
There are no drama teachers
living here.

09:08.298 --> 09:12.552
I mean, I'm assuming the guy's gotta
be, what, five, six feet long.

09:12.719 --> 09:15.764
So I'd have seen him.

09:15.930 --> 09:19.476
Why don't you step inside? Now.

09:25.231 --> 09:28.234
Don't make a sound.
Shh. It's show time.

09:32.113 --> 09:35.658
Kid, I think you're sittin' on my teeth.
Quick, gimme, gimme, gimme. Come on.

09:35.825 --> 09:39.454
Your teeth?
Sick! Gross!

09:41.081 --> 09:42.874
Hey, kid, I owe ya one.

09:43.041 --> 09:46.086
Van Welker!
You in there?

09:47.796 --> 09:50.757
Van Welker!

09:52.383 --> 09:55.595
Van Welker!

09:55.762 --> 09:58.264
Who the hell are you?

09:58.431 --> 10:00.308
Dennis Van Welker?

10:00.475 --> 10:03.311
Well, glad to meet you, Dennis.

10:03.478 --> 10:07.357
The name's T.R. Polk. I'm
looking for Dennis Van Welker.

10:07.524 --> 10:09.901
And according to my
information, you're him.

10:10.068 --> 10:14.155
Sorry, man.
Roland J. Orlando.

10:14.322 --> 10:16.449
Wait a minute!

10:16.616 --> 10:20.370
I bought this here trailer
from a feller named Van Welker.

10:20.537 --> 10:24.124
Yeah? Did this Van
Welker have a "caar"?

10:24.290 --> 10:27.085
Well, I guess he must've to
pull the trailer.

10:29.921 --> 10:35.426
In 1979, Dennis Van Welker bought
a Caribbean yellow Gremlin...

10:35.593 --> 10:38.888
from Rasmunsen's AMC-Jeep
in Columbus, Ohio.

10:39.055 --> 10:42.559
- A yellow Gremlin? - He signed a
contract for 48 equal payments...

10:42.725 --> 10:44.727
of $121 .43.

10:44.894 --> 10:48.398
He made five. We're still
lookin' for the other 43.

10:48.565 --> 10:52.193
- God! What a swine!
- Hey, come on.

10:52.360 --> 10:55.071
Last year, Rasmunsen
sold the debt...

10:55.238 --> 10:58.241
to Bulldog Collections;
that's me.

10:58.408 --> 11:02.370
- Well, Mr. Bulldog.
- Polk. T.R. Polk.

11:02.537 --> 11:06.875
I retire in October. When I go,
I'm goin' with a perfect record.

11:07.041 --> 11:11.713
So no piss-yellow coup is gonna
keep me out of the hall of fame.

11:13.339 --> 11:14.716
Now, what's in the shed?

11:14.883 --> 11:17.969
Look, I really should be gettin'
down to the plant.

11:18.136 --> 11:22.265
Dad! Dad!
Oh, nellie, Dad! It's an emergency!

11:22.432 --> 11:26.311
Uh, the plant just called. Number
three turbine's out of alignment.

11:26.477 --> 11:29.981
Hold your horses there,
Alphonse.

11:30.148 --> 11:33.234
Can't you see I'm helping
this man find a missing car?

11:39.657 --> 11:41.659
Not here.

11:41.826 --> 11:43.703
Of course it ain't.

11:43.870 --> 11:46.289
Sorry about the door.

11:49.125 --> 11:52.128
- Your kid, huh?
- Yup. Heir to the throne.

11:52.295 --> 11:54.881
Well, Van Welker
had no children.

11:55.048 --> 11:57.675
That's a tragedy.

11:57.842 --> 12:00.553
Well, if he turns up, give me a call.
I'd appreciate it.

12:00.720 --> 12:03.223
So would the Ohio State Police.

12:09.646 --> 12:12.065
- Don't hit him, Zack.
- I won't.

12:14.901 --> 12:18.780
You know, you really oughta get the Club.
Any idiot can hot-wire a Gremlin.

12:18.947 --> 12:22.242
What do you want from me?
The car was a dog.

12:22.408 --> 12:26.704
Late at night, I used to hear it barking
in the driveway.

12:26.871 --> 12:30.124
Mr. Van Welker, we don't
care about the car.

12:30.291 --> 12:33.002
How would you like
to make $1,000?

12:33.169 --> 12:35.255
A thousand bucks.
Ha!

12:35.421 --> 12:39.676
Chicken feed! Now, if you'll excuse
me, I gotta go call my broker.

12:39.842 --> 12:43.721
555-0093.

12:43.888 --> 12:45.014
I'm sorry?

12:45.181 --> 12:47.058
Polk's phone number,
Mr. Van Welker.

12:47.225 --> 12:49.519
Oh, I get it.
Shakedown time.

12:49.686 --> 12:52.939
And people say kids today
lack ambition.

12:53.106 --> 12:56.317
A thousand bucks, you say?

12:57.819 --> 12:59.988
Hmm.

13:02.282 --> 13:06.369
Mr. Himmel? Dennis Wozniak,
Binary Pines Computer Camp.

13:06.536 --> 13:08.454
Been expecting ya.
Come on in.

13:08.621 --> 13:10.456
Thanks.

13:15.253 --> 13:17.505
Hey, nice sweater.

13:17.672 --> 13:21.009
In today's job market, you've got to
master the skills of tomorrow, now.

13:21.175 --> 13:25.138
For instance, 379 of the
Fortune 500 companies...

13:25.305 --> 13:28.766
use exactly the same Novell
netware release that we teach.

13:28.933 --> 13:31.519
Here, Mr. Grotowski.

13:31.686 --> 13:35.773
Of course, you should know that our Trish
takes her precious horses pretty seriously.

13:35.940 --> 13:40.111
Acting, Dad! This is theater camp.
Caitlin goes to riding camp.

13:40.278 --> 13:42.196
Of course.

13:42.363 --> 13:45.825
It does sound
interesting, Jerzy.

13:45.992 --> 13:48.536
But she's been so happy at Lake
Broadway, and I think it's,

13:48.703 --> 13:50.788
I don't know, prestigious.

13:50.955 --> 13:54.542
Oh, it
is fine program, Mrs. Prescott.

13:54.709 --> 13:57.337
More than adequate.

13:57.503 --> 14:01.591
But how deep can you go
in, uh, six weeks?

14:01.758 --> 14:06.888
At Camp Sleek-Away, we believe
there are no fat people.

14:07.055 --> 14:09.057
There's fat, and there's people.

14:09.223 --> 14:13.186
Look, whatever dumb diet
you guys use, it won't work.

14:13.353 --> 14:14.604
Shh.

14:14.771 --> 14:17.982
She's right.
Diets don't work.

14:18.149 --> 14:20.276
Chocolate cake works.

14:20.443 --> 14:23.237
Well, it sounds like
a hell of an operation, Savage,

14:23.404 --> 14:27.283
but as I said on the phone, Zachary
will be going back to Camp Steelgrave.

14:27.450 --> 14:31.496
Well, Mr. Dell,
if you're happy with, uh,

14:31.662 --> 14:34.248
Weepy's results,

14:34.415 --> 14:36.584
I won't waste your time.

14:36.751 --> 14:39.545
Weepy?

14:39.712 --> 14:44.008
Just a nickname Sergeant
Steelgrave picked up in 'Nam.

14:44.175 --> 14:46.761
Isn't that interesting, Morris?

14:46.928 --> 14:49.430
You should look up "interesting"
in the dictionary, Dad.

14:49.597 --> 14:50.640
Morris.

14:50.807 --> 14:53.851
You know, Morris, if you were an ordinary
kid, it wouldn't matter so much.

14:54.018 --> 14:56.562
But you've got such...

15:00.608 --> 15:03.277
potential.

15:05.905 --> 15:11.285
And that is why our season
runs two weeks longer.

15:11.452 --> 15:13.913
She'd be gone for eight weeks?

15:14.080 --> 15:16.082
I know it is long time
to be separated.

15:16.249 --> 15:19.544
That means we wouldn't have to
come back from Europe until...

15:19.710 --> 15:22.630
When's Parents' Day?
August?

15:22.797 --> 15:27.093
At Shakespeare Hollow,
we do not have Parents' Day.

15:27.260 --> 15:30.680
We feel it encourages
independence.

15:30.847 --> 15:33.391
Say no more, Jerzy.

15:33.558 --> 15:36.936
I think we just have to do what's
right for our little girl.

15:39.689 --> 15:41.232
Mm-mm-mm-mm-mmm.

15:41.399 --> 15:45.111
It's fantastic!
This is great cake!

15:45.278 --> 15:47.488
It's very unusual.

15:47.655 --> 15:50.867
I'll be right back.

15:51.033 --> 15:54.871
- God, what'd you do?
- Yours is Betty Crocker.

15:55.037 --> 15:58.166
Hers is raw liver paste.

15:58.332 --> 16:02.336
So if it tastes like poison,
it must be diet food.

16:06.799 --> 16:10.136
Son, are you deaf or just stupid?
Answer that phone!

16:10.303 --> 16:12.472
I'm busy.
Get it yourself.

16:12.638 --> 16:14.682
Answer it or eat it, boy.

16:14.849 --> 16:18.769
I see Weepy's worked wonders.

16:18.936 --> 16:24.567
At Alpha Charlie, we scrape
'em down to bare metal.

16:24.734 --> 16:27.236
And it's worth it when they
look up at you and say,

16:27.403 --> 16:31.991
Dad was right, Major Savage.
I am scum.

16:32.158 --> 16:34.744
Answer the phone, son.

16:34.911 --> 16:37.830
Yes, sir.

16:39.457 --> 16:41.792
- Dell residence.
- How's it goin'?

16:41.959 --> 16:44.045
Check or plastic?

16:44.212 --> 16:47.173
- Cash.
- Mission accomplished.

16:47.340 --> 16:49.175
We're in.

16:49.342 --> 16:50.676
Yes!

16:51.469 --> 16:53.888
Feln's Miracle Spa?

16:54.055 --> 16:55.890
Yeah, I found it in the newspaper.

16:56.057 --> 16:58.017
Where? In the obituaries?

16:58.184 --> 17:01.020
Trust me.
It's perfect.

17:01.187 --> 17:04.898
So that's two cabins for the summer.
Am I right?

17:05.066 --> 17:08.319
- If you want more, you gotta call
me in Florida. - So, I don't get it.

17:08.486 --> 17:11.948
- Who built those tepees and
painted that weird bus? - Ahhh!

17:12.114 --> 17:16.035
That's interesting. In the late
'60s, a bunch of hippies...

17:16.202 --> 17:18.746
made this place into a commune.

17:18.913 --> 17:24.001
You know, there was all sorts of
sex and drugs and debauchery.

17:24.167 --> 17:26.712
I knew I'd been here before.

17:26.878 --> 17:30.925
- You mean you did that stuff here?
- No, not here.

17:35.012 --> 17:37.515
You won't regret this,
Mr. Bandersnatch.

17:37.682 --> 17:40.893
You're in for the most peaceful,
relaxing summer...

17:41.060 --> 17:43.729
of your whole lives.

17:49.026 --> 17:52.738
That was the Pineview
Air Force Base.

17:52.905 --> 17:57.368
The 5: 15 flyby,
they call it.

17:57.535 --> 17:59.537
You get used to it.
You get used to it.

17:59.704 --> 18:03.666
Then you miss it when it doesn't happen.

18:03.833 --> 18:06.043
So we should just
take the Greyhound.

18:06.210 --> 18:08.629
The bus?
Why can't we rent a limo?

18:08.796 --> 18:10.881
You know what'd be cool?
We should hitchhike.

18:11.048 --> 18:13.384
Yeah. That would be really cool.

18:13.551 --> 18:18.055
And then we should just, you know, leave our
pictures behind for them to put on the milk cartons.

18:18.222 --> 18:20.308
Hey, guys, I've been checking out
the train schedules. You wanna...

18:22.143 --> 18:24.729
Hold on a second.
I'll be right back.

18:24.895 --> 18:27.148
